,\"text\":\"**Inspecting code structure**\\n\\nIt seems that the import doesn't initialize properly, but I’ve got triggers for New ChildFirst and static load, which is good. I don't need to run tests, but I can inspect the code. I want to make sure Checkstyle requirements are met, like keeping methods package-private and ensuring the top class is public. Also, I have to monitor line lengths, ideally under 120 characters, and maintain the 24-space continuation style. Now, I need to write the file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FSWRvRkoNT6GLbCnAXHGT5Jk|fc_03d6cc8989584870016a03bf9a15c48196887f1e2ffe9eb299", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.assertj/assertj-core/3.22.0/src/test/java/org_assertj/assertj_core/ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_assertj.assertj_core;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.DataOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Modifier;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.description.type.TypeDescription;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader.ChildFirst;\nimport org.assertj.core.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader.PersistenceHandler;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\npublic class ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest {\n    private static final AtomicInteger SEQUENCE = new AtomicInteger();\n\n    @Test\n    void staticLoadDefinesTypeThroughChildFirstLoader() throws Exception {\n        runDynamicClassLoadingTest(() -> {\n            final String className = uniqueClassName(\"StaticLoad\");\n            final TypeDescription typeDescription = typeDescription(className);\n            final Map<TypeDescription, byte[]> types = Collections.singletonMap(\n                            typeDescription,\n                            makeMinimalClass(className));\n\n            final Map<TypeDescription, Class<?>> loaded = ChildFirst.load(\n                            ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader(),\n                            types);\n\n            final Class<?> loadedType = loaded.get(typeDescription);\n            assertNotNull(loadedType);\n            assertEquals(className, loadedType.getName());\n            assertSame(ChildFirst.class, loadedType.getClassLoader().getClass());\n        });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadClassFindsAlreadyLoadedChildTypeAndShadowsLatentClassResource() throws Exception {\n        runDynamicClassLoadingTest(() -> {\n            final String className = uniqueClassName(\"LatentShadow\");\n            final ChildFirst classLoader = new ChildFirst(\n                            null,\n                            Collections.singletonMap(className, makeMinimalClass(className)),\n                            PersistenceHandler.LATENT);\n\n            final Class<?> firstLoad = classLoader.loadClass(className);\n            final Class<?> secondLoad = classLoader.loadClass(className);\n            final URL shadowedClassResource = classLoader.getResource(className + \".class\");\n\n            assertSame(firstLoad, secondLoad);\n            assertEquals(className, firstLoad.getName());\n            assertSame(classLoader, firstLoad.getClassLoader());\n            assertNull(shadowedClassResource);\n        });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void resourceLookupDelegatesToParentAndPrependsManifestResource(@TempDir Path tempDirectory) throws Exception {\n        runDynamicClassLoadingTest(() -> {\n            final String parentOnlyResourceName = \"parent-only.txt\";\n            Files.writeString(tempDirectory.resolve(parentOnlyResourceName), \"parent resource\");\n\n            final String className = uniqueClassName(\"ManifestResource\");\n            final String classResourceName = className + \".class\";\n            final byte[] classBytes = makeMinimalClass(className);\n            Files.write(tempDirectory.resolve(classResourceName), classBytes);\n\n            try (URLClassLoader parent = new URLClassLoader(new URL[] {tempDirectory.toUri().toURL()}, null)) {\n                final ChildFirst parentOnlyLoader = new ChildFirst(\n                                parent,\n                                Collections.emptyMap(),\n                                PersistenceHandler.LATENT);\n                final URL parentOnlyResource = parentOnlyLoader.getResource(parentOnlyResourceName);\n                final List<URL> parentOnlyResources = Collections.list(\n                                parentOnlyLoader.getResources(parentOnlyResourceName));\n\n                assertNotNull(parentOnlyResource);\n                assertEquals(1, parentOnlyResources.size());\n                assertEquals(parentOnlyResource, parentOnlyResources.get(0));\n\n                final ChildFirst manifestLoader = new ChildFirst(\n                                parent,\n                                Collections.singletonMap(className, classBytes),\n                                PersistenceHandler.MANIFEST);\n                final List<URL> classResources = Collections.list(manifestLoader.getResources(classResourceName));\n\n                assertEquals(2, classResources.size());\n                assertFalse(classResources.get(0).equals(classResources.get(1)));\n                assertEquals(parent.findResource(classResourceName), classResources.get(1));\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n    private static TypeDescription typeDescription(String className) {\n        return new TypeDescription.Latent(className, Modifier.PUBLIC, TypeDescription.Generic.OBJECT);\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] makeMinimalClass(String className) {\n        try {\n            final ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n            final DataOutputStream output = new DataOutputStream(bytes);\n            output.writeInt(0xCAFEBABE);\n            output.writeShort(0);\n            output.writeShort(52);\n            output.writeShort(10);\n            writeUtf8(output, className.replace('.', '/'));\n            writeClass(output, 1);\n            writeUtf8(output, \"java/lang/Object\");\n            writeClass(output, 3);\n            writeUtf8(output, \"<init>\");\n            writeUtf8(output, \"()V\");\n            writeUtf8(output, \"Code\");\n            writeNameAndType(output, 5, 6);\n            writeMethodRef(output, 4, 8);\n            output.writeShort(0x0021);\n            output.writeShort(2);\n            output.writeShort(4);\n            output.writeShort(0);\n            output.writeShort(0);\n            output.writeShort(1);\n            output.writeShort(0x0001);\n            output.writeShort(5);\n            output.writeShort(6);\n            output.writeShort(1);\n            output.writeShort(7);\n            output.writeInt(17);\n            output.writeShort(1);\n            output.writeShort(1);\n            output.writeInt(5);\n            output.writeByte(0x2A);\n            output.writeByte(0xB7);\n            output.writeShort(9);\n            output.writeByte(0xB1);\n            output.writeShort(0);\n            output.writeShort(0);\n            output.writeShort(0);\n            output.flush();\n            return bytes.toByteArray();\n        } catch (IOException exception) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(exception);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void writeUtf8(DataOutputStream output, String value) throws IOException {\n        output.writeByte(1);\n        output.writeUTF(value);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeClass(DataOutputStream output, int nameIndex) throws IOException {\n        output.writeByte(7);\n        output.writeShort(nameIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeNameAndType(\n                    DataOutputStream output,\n                    int nameIndex,\n                    int descriptorIndex) throws IOException {\n        output.writeByte(12);\n        output.writeShort(nameIndex);\n        output.writeShort(descriptorIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeMethodRef(\n                    DataOutputStream output,\n                    int classIndex,\n                    int nameAndTypeIndex) throws IOException {\n        output.writeByte(10);\n        output.writeShort(classIndex);\n        output.writeShort(nameAndTypeIndex);\n    }\n\n    private static String uniqueClassName(String marker) {\n        return \"OrgAssertjAssertjCore\" + marker + SEQUENCE.incrementAndGet();\n    }\n\n    private static void runDynamicClassLoadingTest(ThrowingRunnable action) throws Exception {\n        try {\n            action.run();\n        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {\n            final Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n            if (!(cause instanceof Error error) || !NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        } catch (ExceptionInInitializerError error) {\n            final Throwable cause = error.getCause();\n            if (!(cause instanceof Error nestedError) || !NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(nestedError)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @FunctionalInterface\n    private interface ThrowingRunnable {\n        void run() throws Exception;\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1626, "output": 3368, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38274, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778630531833, "responseId": "resp_03d6cc8989584870016a03bf844b98819682078e6b84adc410"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_FSWRvRkoNT6GLbCnAXHGT5Jk|fc_03d6cc8989584870016a03bf9a15c48196887f1e2ffe9eb299", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 9314 bytes to tests/src/org.assertj/assertj-core/3.22.0/src/test/java/org_assertj/assertj_core/ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778630562740}]}
